1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,000
Finally, it was agreed.

2
00:00:01,376 --> 00:00:10,466
The builder would, in effect, advance J.M. the $1,200 to be repaid at $100 a month plus interest.

3
00:00:11,296 --> 00:00:16,145
Now all J.M. had to do was to find $100 a month.

4
00:00:16,496 --> 00:00:23,826
Mr. and Mrs. J.M. sharpened their pencils and figured out a way to cut expenditures $25 a month.

5
00:00:24,096 --> 00:00:29,506
But that still left $75, which J.M. would have to raise each month.

6
00:00:30,096 --> 00:00:32,545
Then, J.M. got another idea.

7
00:00:32,816 --> 00:00:35,506
The next morning, he went in to see his boss.

8
00:00:35,616 --> 00:00:38,706
He explained to his employer what he was doing.

9
00:00:38,896 --> 00:00:43,106
His boss was glad to learn that J.M. was going to buy a new home.

10
00:00:43,456 --> 00:00:51,826
Then J.M. said, Look, Mr. T, to work this deal out, I've got to earn at least $75 more each month.

11
00:00:52,096 --> 00:00:57,746
Now I know, J.M. continued, you'll give me a raise when you feel that I deserve it.

12
00:00:58,016 --> 00:01:01,425
What I want now is just a chance to earn more money.

13
00:01:01,616 --> 00:01:05,265
There are some things around here that could best be done on weekends.

14
00:01:05,376 --> 00:01:08,305
Would you make it possible for me to work then?

15
00:01:09,136 --> 00:01:13,665
The employer was impressed with J.M.'s sincerity and ambition.

16
00:01:13,936 --> 00:01:18,466
He proposed a way for J.M. to work ten extra hours each weekend,

17
00:01:18,496 --> 00:01:22,305
and Mr. and Mrs. J.M. moved into their new home.

18
00:01:23,456 --> 00:01:24,066
1.

19
00:01:24,256 --> 00:01:30,706
The resolution to take action ignited JM's mind to think of ways to accomplish his goal.

20
00:01:30,706 --> 00:01:31,986
2.

21
00:01:32,256 --> 00:01:35,665
JM gained tremendously in new confidence.

22
00:01:35,776 --> 00:01:40,706
It will be much easier for him to take action in other major situations.

23
00:01:40,706 --> 00:01:42,545
3.

24
00:01:43,056 --> 00:01:47,506
J.M. provided his wife and child the living standard they deserved.

25
00:01:47,616 --> 00:01:56,946
Had he waited, postponed buying the house until conditions were perfect, there is a real possibility they never would have owned a home of their own.

26
00:01:58,736 --> 00:02:00,226
Case Number 3.

27
00:02:00,816 --> 00:02:04,466
C.D. wanted to start his own business, but...

28
00:02:05,216 --> 00:02:15,665
Mr. C.D. represents another case of what happens to big ideas when one waits until conditions are perfect before taking action on those ideas.
